                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 24: An empowered group of ministers (EGoM) has resolved the issue of allowing tax benefits to an Essar SEZ, which allegedly violated the rules of the SEZ Act. The EGoM, which met under the chairmanship of external affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee, decided to condone the act of the promoter to begin development on the site before it got formal approval from the Centre.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 24: Coal availability at thermal power stations has reached a critical level with as many as 35 stations having stocks of less than four days, a problem that can lead to the closure of some of the plants. The all-India coal stock at power stations depleted from 11.04 million tonnes (mt) on April, 2008 to 4.86mt on October 19, power minister Sushilkumar Shinde said in the Lok Sabha.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 24: Unitech is in talks with global telecom players to divest 26-45 per cent stake of its telecom unit within a month. The deal is likely to be finalised within this month, Unitech managing director Sanjay Chandra said.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 24: NTPC has posted a 9.6 per cent rise in net profit for the second quarter ended September 30 at Rs 2,110.51 crore. Total income rose 18.94 per cent to Rs 10,406.21 crore during the quarter. For the six months ended September 30, NTPC reported a net profit of Rs 3,837.04 crore, a 10.67 per cent decline over the year-ago period.                                                                                                                         
